Theek hai bhai üòé, simple style me bataata hu kaise use karna hai **button me**:

---

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ CSS bana lo

```css
/* styles.css ya component ke CSS file me */
.disabled-btn {
  background-color: gray;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.active-btn {
  background-color: orange;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Button HTML me ngClass use karo

```html
<button
  [ngClass]="{ 'disabled-btn': !email || !password, 'active-btn': email && password }"
  [disabled]="!email || !password">
  Login
</button>
```

* `[ngClass]` ‚Üí decide karta hai kaunsi class apply hogi.
* `[disabled]` ‚Üí button disable ya enable karega, same condition ke saath.

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Component me variables define karo

```ts
email = '';
password = '';
```

* Ye variables input fields se bind honge `(ngModel)` ke through.
* Jaise hi user input karega, button ki class automatically change ho jaayegi.

---

Bhai, isse button **dynamic color aur enable/disable dono** kaam karenge.

Agar chaahe to mai **full login form ka example** `ngClass` ke saath bana ke dikha du.

